{{Infobox journal | title = Études Phénoménologiques | editors = Pol Vandevelde and Danielle Lories | discipline = [[Philosophy]] | language = English, French | abbreviation = Études Phénoménol. | publisher = [[Peeters (publishing company)|Peeters]] | country = Belgium | frequency = Annual | history = 1985–2008; 2017-present | website = http://poj.peeters-leuven.be/content.php?url=journal&journal_code=EPH | link2-name = https://www.marquette.edu/pheno-studies/index.php https://uclouvain.be/fr/instituts-recherche/isp/cep/etudes-phenomenologiques-phenomenological-studies.html | link3-name = https://uclouvain.be/fr/instituts-recherche/isp/cep/etudes-phenomenologiques-phenomenological-studies.html | link4-name = https://poj.peeters-leuven.be/content.php?url=journal&journal_code=EPH | link5-name = https://www.pdcnet.org/etudphen | OCLC = 12876393 | JSTOR = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0773-7912 | eISSN = 2033-656X }} '''''Études Phénoménologiques''''' (English: '''''Phenomenological Studies''''') is a yearly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] originally published in French by [[Éditions Ousia]]. The journal was founded in 1985 by [[Jacques Taminiaux]] edited it until its closure in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pdcnet.org/etudphen/%C3%89tudes-Ph%C3%A9nom%C3%A9nologiques|title=Études Phénoménologiques|publisher=[[Philosophy Documentation Center]]}}</ref>
In 2017, the publication was rebooted by the Centre d’Études Phénoménologiques of the [[Université catholique de Louvain]] in Belgium and by the Department of Philosophy at [[Marquette University]], in Milwaukee, USA. The reboot is published by [[Peeters (publishing company)|Peeters]] and edited by Pol Vandevelde and Danielle Lories.
